02930nam a22004455i 9780773571099DE-B159720230529101353.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||230529t20032003xxc    fo  d z      eng d  a97807735710997 a10.1515/97807735710992doi  a(DE-B1597)656329  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  axxccCA 4aJA85.2.C2bB587 2003eb 7aPOL0180002bisacsh04a320.9711 aBlattberg, Charles, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aShall We Dance? :bA Patriotic Politics for Canada /cCharles Blattberg. 1aMontreal ;aKingston ;aLondon ;aChicago : bMcGill-Queen's University Press, c[2003] 4cÂ©2003  a1 online resource (160 p.)  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFront Matter -- tContents -- tPreface -- tIntroduction: A Canadian Home? -- tResponding to Conflict: Three Ways, Three Canadas -- tWho We Were -- tWho We Are -- tWho We Could Be -- tConclusion: Divide and Listen -- tNotes -- tBibliography -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aCharles Blattberg shows that while a just politics based on dialogue is at the core of Canadians' sense of ourselves as citizens, our current forms of dialogue are inadequate. To some, we should be pleading before authorities responsible for upholding a unified foundation for our politics. Pierre Trudeau and his followers, for example, advocate a Charter of Rights and Freedoms that trumps any values not contained within it. To others, we ought to be true to the longstanding Canadian political tradition of compromise and so negotiate our conflicts, a form of dialogue that strives for accommodation rather than trumping. Blattberg argues, however, that both of these approaches have largely failed us. To him, the preferred form of dialogue in Canadian politics today should be that of conversation. As he shows, only conversation aims for the genuine reconciliation of conflict; only it will help us realize the common good that is at the heart of a truly patriotic Canadian politics.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Mai 2023) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Reference.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978077357109940uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780773571099423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780773571099/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles